==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intranuclear
<hw>In`tra*nu"cle*ar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to, or located on the inside of a nucleus; taking
place within a nucleus; referring especially to the nucleus of a cell;
<as>as, the <ex>intranuclear</ex> network of fibrils, seen in the first
stages of karyokinesis</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intrap</ent>⟦br⟧
